[upbeat surf rock]

00:04.838 --> 00:11.177
♪ ♪

00:11.261 --> 00:12.429
- ♪ WE ARE RIDERS ♪

00:12.512 --> 00:13.263
♪ ON A MISSION ♪

00:13.346 --> 00:16.641
♪ ACTION KIDS
IN PLAY POSITION ♪

00:16.725 --> 00:17.726
♪<i> ROCKET POWER</i> ♪

00:17.809 --> 00:18.476
♪ ♪

00:18.560 --> 00:20.311
[record scratches]

00:20.395 --> 00:25.275
♪ ♪

00:25.358 --> 00:26.943
[engines revving]

00:27.026 --> 00:34.242
♪ ♪

00:34.325 --> 00:35.618
♪ WE ARE RIDERS ♪

00:35.702 --> 00:37.078
♪ ON A MISSION ♪

00:37.162 --> 00:39.664
{\an8}♪ ACTION KIDS
IN FUN CONDITION ♪

00:39.748 --> 00:41.499
{\an8}♪ PREPARE
TO COUNT DOWN ♪

00:41.583 --> 00:44.210
{\an8}♪<i> ROCKET POWER</i> ♪

00:44.294 --> 00:46.713
{\an8}[seagulls screeching]

00:56.723 --> 00:58.266
- [yells]

00:59.851 --> 01:01.311
[both gasp]

01:06.900 --> 01:09.694
- PLEASE, PLEASE,
NO AUTOGRAPHS.

01:09.778 --> 01:11.821
{\an8}- OTTO, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO GET ANOTHER SNOWBOARD

01:11.905 --> 01:13.907
{\an8}TO CART THAT HEAD
OF YOURS AROUND.

01:13.990 --> 01:15.492
- IT WAS JUST A 360.

01:15.575 --> 01:17.577
- JUST A 360?

01:17.660 --> 01:19.370
- CAN'T YOU EVER
JUST ENJOY THE RIDE,

01:19.454 --> 01:20.371
ROCKET BOY?

01:20.455 --> 01:21.539
- NO.

01:21.623 --> 01:23.208
- HEY,
CHECK OUT THE SQUID!

01:29.380 --> 01:30.423
- NAILED IT.

01:30.507 --> 01:34.135
- COME ON.

01:34.219 --> 01:35.428
GOT TO CHECK THIS OUT.

01:35.512 --> 01:37.013
- ACTUALLY, WE DON'T.

01:37.096 --> 01:38.515
- I DON'T KNOW, OTTO.

01:38.598 --> 01:39.516
- LOOKS DANGEROUS.

01:39.599 --> 01:42.602
- LAME, LAMER, LAMEST.

01:42.685 --> 01:44.187
SHEESH.

01:47.607 --> 01:48.858
- OOH!

01:53.238 --> 01:54.489
- THE BIG AIR.

01:54.572 --> 01:56.825
- AWESOME.

01:56.908 --> 01:59.285
- TERRIFYING.

01:59.369 --> 02:00.870
- MORE SPEED, BENNY.

02:00.954 --> 02:02.455
SPEED, SPEED!

02:02.539 --> 02:04.332
- HELLO,
EARTH TO OTTO.

02:04.415 --> 02:06.334
COME IN, OTTO.

02:06.417 --> 02:07.794
- ROCKET BOY LAUNCHING.

02:07.877 --> 02:10.088
WHOA, TRIPLE FLIP
WITH A ONE-HALF TWIST.

02:10.170 --> 02:11.881
HE'S GONNA BE--

02:11.965 --> 02:13.716
- GROUNDED.

02:13.800 --> 02:15.051
- OH, MAN,
IT'S LANCE,

02:15.134 --> 02:16.803
THE SKI PATROL DUDE.

02:16.886 --> 02:20.223
- THE BIG AIR'S
FOR EXPERIENCED ADULTS ONLY.

02:20.306 --> 02:21.516
WHEN IT OPENS TOMORROW,

02:21.599 --> 02:22.392
I DON'T WANT TO SEE YOU KIDS
ANYWHERE NEAR IT.

02:22.475 --> 02:24.310
- BUT--

02:24.394 --> 02:25.728
- STAY OUT OF TROUBLE NOW.

02:25.812 --> 02:28.273
- TOLD YOU WE'D GET IN TROUBLE.

02:28.356 --> 02:29.816
- LIKE HE WAS SERIOUS.

02:29.899 --> 02:33.319
COME ON, YOU GUYS.

02:33.403 --> 02:34.070
- WEATHER REPORT SAYS
WE'RE GONNA GET

02:34.153 --> 02:37.073
A COUPLE OF INCHES
OF SNOW TONIGHT.

02:37.156 --> 02:41.411
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE REST UP
AND HIT THAT FRESH POWDER

02:41.494 --> 02:42.412
TOMORROW MORNING.

02:42.495 --> 02:47.750
- [snoring]

02:47.834 --> 02:51.296
- ONCE AGAIN, YOU'RE WAY AHEAD
OF ME, BROTHER.

02:54.883 --> 02:55.592
- REPEAT AFTER ME.

02:55.675 --> 02:57.635
AH-HUH!

02:57.719 --> 03:00.763
- AH-HUH!

03:00.847 --> 03:01.598
- AH-HUH.

03:01.681 --> 03:03.558
- YOU'RE OUT, SQUID.

03:03.641 --> 03:05.059
ONE DOWN, TWO TO GO.

03:05.143 --> 03:05.184
FOLLOW ME.

03:08.646 --> 03:10.940
HA, TOLD YA.

03:11.024 --> 03:12.692
- LOOKS LIKE IT'S JUST
YOU AND ME, ROCKET BOY.

03:12.775 --> 03:15.194
- NOT FOR LONG, REG.

03:15.278 --> 03:17.447
REPEAT AFTER ME.

03:18.448 --> 03:20.617
- [yawns]

03:20.700 --> 03:24.454
YOU'LL HAVE TO DO
BETTER THAN THAT.

03:24.537 --> 03:27.206
[both grunting]

03:42.221 --> 03:43.640
- THIS'LL DUMP HER.

03:49.228 --> 03:50.480
- [laughs]

03:50.563 --> 03:51.689
GOOD GAME, ROCKET BOY.

03:51.773 --> 03:52.982
WE'LL CALL IT A TIE.

03:53.066 --> 03:53.691
{\an8}- TIE?

03:53.775 --> 03:55.652
POWER ROCKET DOESN'T TIE.

03:55.735 --> 03:58.863
- YOU DID THIS TIME.

03:58.947 --> 03:59.989
- EVERYONE KNOWS A TIE
GOES TO THE LEADER.

04:00.073 --> 04:03.117
- WHAT KIND OF
STUPID RULE IS THAT?

04:03.201 --> 04:04.661
- A GOOD RULE.

04:04.744 --> 04:06.037
- I THINK HE'S RIGHT, REG.

04:06.120 --> 04:08.456
- WHAT OTHER PROOF
DO I NEED?

04:08.539 --> 04:10.124
- YOU KNOW,
I READ ONCE--

04:10.208 --> 04:11.042
- LOOK, I WON.

04:11.125 --> 04:11.626
END OF STORY,
GAME OVER.

04:11.709 --> 04:13.711
- GAME OVER?

04:13.795 --> 04:14.504
LET'S PLAY AGAIN,

04:14.587 --> 04:16.839
AND THIS TIME
I'LL BE THE LEADER.

04:16.923 --> 04:17.423
- IN YOUR DREAMS.

04:17.507 --> 04:19.384
I WON.

04:19.466 --> 04:20.551
YOU LOST.

04:20.635 --> 04:22.136
GET USED TO IT.

04:22.220 --> 04:22.679
- OTTO, DON'T.

04:22.762 --> 04:24.180
- OH, MAN!

04:24.263 --> 04:28.184
- OTTO, I CAN BEAT YOU
ANY TIME, ANYWHERE,

04:28.267 --> 04:31.604
IN ANY SPORT, LITTLE BRO.

04:31.688 --> 04:33.314
- BRING IT ON, REGINA.

04:44.701 --> 04:45.743
- WHAT?

04:45.827 --> 04:47.370
TITO?

04:47.453 --> 04:51.249
TITO?

04:51.332 --> 04:51.791
- NOT NOW, BROTHER.

04:51.874 --> 04:54.544
I'M SURFING PIPELINE.

04:54.627 --> 04:56.421
[snores]

04:59.132 --> 05:00.091
- HERE THEY COME,

05:00.174 --> 05:00.675
AND REGGIE'S IN THE LEAD.

05:00.758 --> 05:02.719
- YEAH, RIGHT.

05:08.391 --> 05:10.184
- EAT MY SNOW!

05:16.232 --> 05:17.775
[panting]

05:17.859 --> 05:18.901
- OTTO, LOW FIVE, BRO.

05:18.985 --> 05:19.944
WOOGEDY-WOOGEDY.

05:20.028 --> 05:21.154
YOU THE MAN!

05:21.237 --> 05:22.322
- THAT I AM.

05:22.405 --> 05:23.281
- ARE YOU BLIND?

05:23.364 --> 05:24.907
REGGIE WON BY A MILE.

05:24.991 --> 05:25.825
- YEAH.

05:25.908 --> 05:27.660
- ARE YOU SAYING I LOST?

05:27.744 --> 05:30.413
- I'M SAYING YOU CAME
IN SECOND OUT OF TWO!

05:30.496 --> 05:31.581
- GUYS, WE NEED
AN OFFICIAL JUDGE.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.666
- ALL RISE.

05:33.750 --> 05:36.502
THE TWISTER'S COURT
IS NOW IN SESSION.

05:48.097 --> 05:48.556
WHOA.

05:51.684 --> 05:54.604
WHOA!

05:54.687 --> 05:56.230
- COURT IS ADJOURNED.

06:02.111 --> 06:05.490
- MONSTER JUMP, OTTOMAN!

06:05.573 --> 06:07.366
- REGGIE'S GONNA WASTE HIM.

06:14.082 --> 06:14.707
[both growl]

06:14.791 --> 06:18.795
- WHO WINS?

06:18.878 --> 06:21.047
- [chuckles]

06:30.098 --> 06:33.226
[camera timer rings]

06:33.309 --> 06:36.229
- [yells]

06:40.399 --> 06:44.320
- OKAY, IT'S A TEST OF SPEED,
SKILL, AND GUTS.

06:44.403 --> 06:45.655
WE FLY DOWN THE MOUNTAIN

06:45.738 --> 06:48.324
USING ALL THOSE KOOKS
LIKE SLALOM GATES.

06:48.407 --> 06:50.034
FIRST ONE TO THE
SKI LIFT WINS.

06:50.118 --> 06:51.661
MEANING ME.

06:51.744 --> 06:53.329
- OTTO,
YOU BETTER WATCH OUT.

06:53.412 --> 06:55.039
THERE'S A LOT OF PEOPLE
ON THIS RUN.

06:55.123 --> 06:56.874
- TWO RULES, ROCKET BOY.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.668
NO CHEATING
WHEN YOU FALL BEHIND,

06:58.751 --> 07:02.171
AND NO CRYING
WHEN YOU LOSE.

07:02.255 --> 07:03.631
- ON YOUR MARK,
GET SET.

07:03.714 --> 07:06.259
- GO HOME.

07:06.342 --> 07:08.511
- NO, IT'S "GO."

07:08.594 --> 07:10.680
ON YOUR MARK, GET SET--

07:10.763 --> 07:12.849
- THIS RACE IS CANCELLED.

07:12.932 --> 07:14.475
- RACE,
WHAT RACE?

07:14.559 --> 07:16.853
- GET ON THE GONDOLA
AND RIDE BACK DOWN.

07:16.936 --> 07:19.522
YOU KIDS ARE DONE
FOR THE DAY.

07:19.605 --> 07:20.898
- YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

07:20.982 --> 07:23.442
- HEY, IT'S EITHER THAT
OR I TAKE YOUR LIFT TICKETS AWAY

07:23.526 --> 07:24.777
AND PUT 'EM
ON THE WALL OF SHAME.

07:24.861 --> 07:26.320
YOUR CHOICE.

07:26.404 --> 07:27.697
- WALL OF SHAME?

07:27.780 --> 07:29.073
- THEY TAKE AWAY
YOUR PASS.

07:29.157 --> 07:31.701
THEY PUT IT UP ON THE WALL
SO EVERYBODY CAN LAUGH AT YOU.

07:31.784 --> 07:34.162
IT'S A SHREDDER'S
WORST NIGHTMARE.

07:34.245 --> 07:37.540
- SO WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

07:40.334 --> 07:42.962
- YOU'RE LUCKY
HE CAME ALONG, OTTO.

07:43.045 --> 07:44.881
SAVED YOU
A LOT OF HUMILIATION.

07:57.894 --> 07:59.812
- WHOA!

07:59.896 --> 08:02.148
LOOK AT THE BIG AIR
THOSE GUYS ARE GETTING!

08:02.231 --> 08:04.317
I WANT SOME OF THAT AIR.

08:04.400 --> 08:05.902
- DO YOU EVER STOP?

08:05.985 --> 08:09.322
I SWEAR THEY OUGHT TO CALL YOU
THE BIG AIRHEAD.

08:09.405 --> 08:12.909
- HEY, THAT'S HOW
WE CAN SETTLE THIS.

08:12.992 --> 08:15.703
YOU AND ME, THE BIG AIR.

08:15.786 --> 08:17.538
WINNER TAKES ALL.

08:17.622 --> 08:20.249
- BUT LANCE SAID HE'LL PUT US
ON THE WALL OF SHAME.

08:20.333 --> 08:23.377
MY FRAGILE PSYCHE CAN'T HANDLE
THAT HUMILIATION.

08:25.671 --> 08:29.383
- THEN WE'LL HIT IT AT SUNRISE
BEFORE LANCE IS EVEN HERE.

08:29.467 --> 08:30.676
HOW ABOUT IT?

08:30.760 --> 08:35.181
- THE FIRST ANNUAL OTTO ROCKET
BIG AIR DARE IS ON, BABY!

08:41.854 --> 08:44.607
[wind howling]

08:47.151 --> 08:49.612
YOU SCARED YET?

08:49.695 --> 08:51.030
- NO,
NO WAY.

08:51.113 --> 08:51.948
LET'S DO IT.

08:52.031 --> 08:54.742
- WAIT, REGGIE, OTTO,
PLEASE LISTEN TO ME.

08:54.825 --> 08:57.662
WE'RE ALL ALONE UP HERE.

08:57.745 --> 09:00.706
- HA,
I KNEW YOU'D WIMP OUT.

09:05.711 --> 09:06.963
- IT'S ALL COME DOWN
TO THIS,

09:07.046 --> 09:10.925
AS ROCKET BOY AND ROCKET GIRL
ATTEMPT THE BIG AIR DARE.

09:11.008 --> 09:11.968
- GO, REGGIE!

09:12.051 --> 09:12.927
GO, OTTO!

09:13.010 --> 09:13.636
BE CAREFUL.

09:13.719 --> 09:17.306
OH, MAN,
I'M ALL ALONE UP HERE.

09:17.390 --> 09:19.350
OH, MAN.

09:19.433 --> 09:21.143
AHH!

09:21.227 --> 09:22.687
- UGH!

09:22.770 --> 09:23.771
[gasps]

09:25.231 --> 09:26.148
- I WIN!

09:26.232 --> 09:28.567
I WIN!

09:28.651 --> 09:30.569
{\an8}UGH!

09:36.450 --> 09:37.743
- OH, MAN.

09:37.827 --> 09:39.245
TOTAL YARD SALE.

09:39.328 --> 09:41.247
OTTO POPPED A BINDING.

09:41.330 --> 09:42.665
- I THINK HE POPPED
MORE THAN THAT.

09:42.748 --> 09:43.582
- OTTO!

09:43.666 --> 09:47.586
ROCKET BOY,
ARE YOU OKAY?

09:47.670 --> 09:47.878
- [groans]

09:47.962 --> 09:50.506
MY LEG.

09:50.589 --> 09:51.507
- LET ME SEE.

09:51.591 --> 09:51.924
LET ME SEE!
- OW!

09:52.008 --> 09:54.218
DON'T TOUCH IT!

09:54.302 --> 09:55.219
- DON'T TOUCH HIM.

09:55.303 --> 09:56.262
DON'T MOVE HIM.

09:56.345 --> 09:57.263
HE'S IN PAIN.

09:57.346 --> 10:00.891
- OTTO, OTTO!

10:00.975 --> 10:01.392
OH, MAN.

10:01.475 --> 10:05.229
SON, IT'LL BE OKAY.

10:05.313 --> 10:06.856
IT'S BROKEN.

10:06.939 --> 10:08.816
TITO,
WILL YOU GO GET HELP?

10:08.899 --> 10:12.236
- YOU GOT IT, BROTHER.

10:12.320 --> 10:13.321
- [groans]

10:13.404 --> 10:17.158
OW.

10:19.118 --> 10:24.832
OW, DAD, IT HURTS SO BAD!

10:24.915 --> 10:25.833
- YOU'LL BE OKAY, OTTO.

10:25.916 --> 10:28.252
- I'M AFRAID YOU'RE NOT
GONNA BE SNOWBOARDING

10:28.336 --> 10:29.754
FOR SOME TIME, KID.

10:29.837 --> 10:31.922
SIR, I TOLD YOUR KIDS
THAT JUMP WAS OFF LIMITS.

10:32.006 --> 10:33.716
- YOU DID?

10:33.799 --> 10:35.384
REGGIE?

10:35.468 --> 10:36.719
- H.Q., THIS IS LANCE.

10:36.802 --> 10:37.720
OVER.

10:37.803 --> 10:40.389
WE HAVE A CODE GREEN
AT THE BIG AIR JUMP.

10:40.473 --> 10:41.557
- SORRY, DAD.
- WE HAVE A MALE SNOWBOARDER,

10:41.640 --> 10:42.892
APPROXIMATELY
NINE YEARS OLD,

10:42.975 --> 10:44.352
WITH A POSSIBLE FRACTURE.

10:49.315 --> 10:52.026
- OH, MAN,
IT'S BAD ENOUGH I BROKE MY LEG.

10:52.109 --> 10:53.819
DO I HAVE TO SIT HERE
AND WATCH YOU GUYS

10:53.903 --> 10:54.403
JUST SITTING AROUND?

10:54.487 --> 10:56.280
WHY DON'T YOU GO UP THERE

10:56.364 --> 10:58.657
AND SKI OR SNOWBOARD
OR SOMETHING?

10:58.741 --> 11:02.119
- IF YOU ASK ME, THIS IS CRUEL
AND UNUSUAL PUNISHMENT.

11:02.203 --> 11:04.622
- I BELIEVE IT WAS AN
ANCIENT HAWAIIAN WHO SAID,

11:04.705 --> 11:09.210
"DON'T DO THE CRIME
IF YOU CAN'T DO THE TIME."

11:09.293 --> 11:10.628
RIGHT, BROTHER?

11:10.711 --> 11:14.006
- ALOHA TO THAT,
TITO, MY MAN.

11:14.090 --> 11:15.091
- MAN,
THIS THING ITCHES.

11:15.174 --> 11:17.343
[yells]

11:17.426 --> 11:18.928
I'M GONNA GO CRAZY!

11:19.011 --> 11:21.639
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
FOR SIX WEEKS?

11:21.722 --> 11:23.599
- RELAX, LITTLE BROTHER.

11:23.682 --> 11:27.395
SIT BACK AND
SMELL THE ROSES.

11:27.478 --> 11:28.437
- ROSES?

11:28.521 --> 11:30.439
I'M ALLERGIC TO ROSES.

11:30.523 --> 11:32.483
[sneezing]

11:36.278 --> 11:38.239
- [chuckles]
- SQUID!

11:38.322 --> 11:39.990
[laughter]

11:43.369 --> 11:46.414
[crowd laughing and jeering]

11:58.384 --> 12:01.429
{\an8}[upbeat surf rock]

12:01.512 --> 12:09.478
{\an8}♪ ♪

12:13.899 --> 12:15.985
{\an8}- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

12:16.068 --> 12:18.863
{\an8}SO MUCH AIR!

12:18.946 --> 12:20.990
AHH!

12:21.073 --> 12:22.074
SO MUCH PAIN.

12:22.158 --> 12:24.535
[laughter]

12:24.618 --> 12:25.578
- YEAH, WHOO-HOO!

12:25.661 --> 12:27.163
ALL RIGHT, YEAH.

12:27.246 --> 12:28.998
- YEAH!

12:29.081 --> 12:30.624
- NO!

12:30.708 --> 12:32.168
[grunts]

12:40.259 --> 12:44.305
HEY, GUYS, IT'S THE RETURN
OF ROCKET BOY.

12:44.388 --> 12:46.474
- YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

12:46.557 --> 12:50.311
- SERIOUS AS A BROKEN LEG.

12:50.394 --> 12:52.313
- I DON'T THINK
IT'S GONNA WORK, BRO.

12:52.396 --> 12:53.397
- IT'LL WORK.

12:53.481 --> 12:55.149
- YOU KNOW,
IT MIGHT JUST WORK.

12:55.232 --> 12:57.151
- HUH?
- SEE?

12:57.234 --> 13:01.780
- IN A PARALLEL UNIVERSE
WHERE BAD IDEAS REALLY WORK.

13:01.864 --> 13:03.782
{\an8}all: BUST!

13:03.866 --> 13:06.368
- OTTO, DO YOU WANT
ANOTHER BROKEN LEG?

13:06.452 --> 13:08.037
- I KNOW I DON'T WANT
TO HEAR HIM CRY AGAIN.

13:08.120 --> 13:10.039
- ME EITHER.

13:10.122 --> 13:10.456
IT WAS GROSS.

13:10.539 --> 13:15.586
- I DIDN'T CRY.

13:15.669 --> 13:16.629
WELL, I WOULDN'T HAVE
BROKEN MY LEG

13:16.712 --> 13:20.216
IF YOU HADN'T MADE ME
GO OFF THAT JUMP.

13:20.299 --> 13:23.636
- I MADE YOU GO OFF
THAT JUMP?

13:23.719 --> 13:25.596
- IT'S OKAY
BECAUSE MY LEG'S PROTECTED

13:25.679 --> 13:29.058
BY THE SPACE-AGE TECHNOLOGY
OF THIS CAST.

13:29.141 --> 13:31.560
OW!

13:31.644 --> 13:33.896
- I HOPE THAT CAST IS
AS THICK AS YOUR SKULL.

13:33.979 --> 13:35.981
- OTTO,
YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T.

13:36.065 --> 13:39.777
- EVERYBODY FREEZE.

13:39.860 --> 13:42.655
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?

13:42.738 --> 13:44.281
- JUST PLAYING
IN THE BACKYARD.

13:44.365 --> 13:45.282
- PLAYING?

13:45.366 --> 13:46.367
IN A CAST?

13:46.450 --> 13:47.743
ON A SKATEBOARD?

13:47.826 --> 13:50.204
YOUR LEG IS BROKEN
IN THREE PLACES.

13:50.287 --> 13:51.830
- BUT IT FEELS BETTER
ALREADY.

13:51.914 --> 13:51.956
OW.

13:56.043 --> 13:56.377
- HEY, REGGIE, I'M OPEN.

13:56.460 --> 13:59.505
- HERE WE GO.

14:05.261 --> 14:06.554
NICE TRY, TWIST.

14:06.637 --> 14:07.680
WE JUST NEED
ANOTHER PLAYER

14:07.763 --> 14:09.598
TO REPLACE OTTO
WHILE HE'S HURT.

14:09.682 --> 14:11.767
- YEAH, BUT I WISH
OTTO COULD PLAY.

14:11.850 --> 14:12.726
- WHAT?

14:12.810 --> 14:13.852
ARE YOU NUTS?

14:13.936 --> 14:15.145
- I MEAN, THE OLD OTTO.

14:15.229 --> 14:17.773
NOT THE NEW,
LESS-IMPROVED OTTO.

14:17.856 --> 14:20.776
- HEY, GUYS,
I'M BACK IN ACTION.

14:20.859 --> 14:22.778
- YOU MEAN BACK IN TRACTION.

14:22.861 --> 14:25.114
- IT'S THE MASTER OF DISASTER.

14:25.197 --> 14:27.283
- LOOK AT ME.

14:27.366 --> 14:29.868
JUST TOOK ABOUT AN HOUR
TO GET THE OLD UNIFORM ON.

14:29.952 --> 14:31.245
NO PROBLEMO.

14:31.328 --> 14:33.122
- OTTO, BAD.

14:33.205 --> 14:34.665
BAD IDEA.

14:34.748 --> 14:35.499
- YOU GUYS DIDN'T FORGET,
DID YOU?

14:35.583 --> 14:38.294
WE GOT THE BIG GAME
ON THURSDAY.

14:38.377 --> 14:40.963
- NO, NOT EXACTLY.

14:41.046 --> 14:42.214
- TWIST, PASS IT!

14:52.266 --> 14:54.685
OW.

14:56.604 --> 14:58.022
- OKAY, THERE'S NO WAY

14:58.105 --> 14:59.356
WE CAN LET OTTO PLAY
IN THE GAME TOMORROW.

14:59.440 --> 15:01.609
both: RIGHT.

15:01.692 --> 15:02.901
- IT'S BAD FOR HIM.

15:02.985 --> 15:04.278
- AND BAD FOR THE TEAM.

15:04.361 --> 15:05.738
- RIGHT.

15:05.821 --> 15:09.158
- SO TWIST, YOU JUST GOT
TO TELL HIM HE CAN'T PLAY.

15:09.241 --> 15:11.160
- I'M NOT GONNA TELL HIM.

15:11.243 --> 15:12.786
- JUST MAKE UP SOME STORY.

15:12.870 --> 15:14.788
- TELL HIM THE RATS
ATE THE PUCK.

15:14.872 --> 15:18.125
- NO, IT'S GOT TO BE
SOMETHING BELIEVABLE

15:18.208 --> 15:20.836
LIKE GLOBAL WARMING
HAS CAUSED GIANT MONKEYS

15:20.919 --> 15:22.254
TO OVERTAKE OCEAN SHORES.

15:22.338 --> 15:23.213
- GIANT MONKEYS?

15:23.297 --> 15:27.343
[screams]

15:27.426 --> 15:29.470
- HE'LL BE BACK.

15:29.553 --> 15:31.680
- LET ME HANDLE THIS,
OKAY?

15:36.977 --> 15:38.187
OH, MAN!

15:38.270 --> 15:40.356
I AM SO TICKED!

15:40.439 --> 15:41.440
- WHAT'S UP?

15:41.523 --> 15:42.775
- THE BIG GAME.

15:42.858 --> 15:44.735
THEY'RE RESCHEDULING IT.

15:44.818 --> 15:46.028
- NO WAY!

15:46.111 --> 15:48.280
WHEN'S IT GONNA BE?

15:48.364 --> 15:51.075
- UM,
THEY HAVEN'T TOLD US,

15:51.158 --> 15:54.620
BUT IT'S DEFINITELY
NOT GONNA BE TOMORROW.

15:54.703 --> 15:56.372
NO, SIR,
NOT TOMORROW.

15:56.455 --> 15:59.208
- THAT STINKS.

15:59.291 --> 16:02.711
- TELL ME ABOUT IT.

16:02.795 --> 16:05.464
[relieved sigh]

16:07.925 --> 16:09.385
- SO?

16:09.468 --> 16:11.178
- WELL, OTTO'S OUT
OF THE PICTURE,

16:11.261 --> 16:13.889
BUT WE STILL
HAVE A PROBLEM.

16:13.972 --> 16:15.224
- THE MONKEYS.

16:15.307 --> 16:17.726
[groans]

16:17.810 --> 16:20.229
- WE STILL NEED SOMEONE
TO FILL IN FOR OTTO.

16:20.312 --> 16:21.772
- YOU GOT SOMEBODY
IN MIND?

16:21.855 --> 16:25.567
- I DO, BUT YOU'RE NOT
GONNA LIKE IT.

16:30.280 --> 16:32.449
SO LOOK, I KNOW
THIS IS WEIRD AND EVERYTHING,

16:32.533 --> 16:35.035
US ASKING FOR HELP...

16:35.119 --> 16:36.995
- BUT THERE'S NO ONE ELSE
WE COULD TURN TO.

16:37.079 --> 16:40.499
- YEAH, I REALLY THOUGHT
WE HAD A SHOT AT THIS,

16:40.582 --> 16:43.085
ESPECIALLY SINCE YOUR TEAM
IS ALREADY ELIMINATED.

16:49.091 --> 16:51.301
- [cackles]

16:54.596 --> 16:55.472
- WHOO-HOO!

16:55.556 --> 16:56.056
YEAH,
ALL RIGHT!

17:01.812 --> 17:02.438
- AHH!

17:02.521 --> 17:08.026
[both panting]

17:08.109 --> 17:10.194
- I DON'T KNOW
IF ASKING HIM TO PLAY

17:10.279 --> 17:11.739
WAS SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

17:11.821 --> 17:14.450
- WITH HIM ON THE TEAM,
AT LEAST WE HAVE A CHANCE.

17:14.532 --> 17:17.161
- WHO KNEW IT WOULD BE
SO EASY TO REPLACE OTTO?

17:17.243 --> 17:20.705
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

17:20.789 --> 17:22.540
- HEY, OTTO.
- HI, OTTO.

17:22.624 --> 17:24.126
- LITTLE BRO.

17:24.209 --> 17:26.170
- WHO'S REPLACING ME?

17:26.252 --> 17:27.421
FOR WHAT?

17:27.503 --> 17:28.589
- BIG MOUTH.

17:28.672 --> 17:30.924
- UM, NOT FOR
THE STREET HOCKEY GAME.

17:31.008 --> 17:32.634
- THE ONE
THAT WAS RESCHEDULED?

17:32.718 --> 17:34.136
- NO, THE ONE TOMORROW.

17:34.219 --> 17:35.804
both: TWISTER!

17:35.888 --> 17:37.514
- OOPS.

17:37.598 --> 17:41.059
- YOU GUYS LIED TO ME?

17:41.143 --> 17:44.062
- OTTO, I CAN EXPLAIN.

17:44.146 --> 17:46.064
- TELL IT
TO SOMEONE WHO CARES.

17:52.613 --> 17:53.947
OW.

17:54.031 --> 17:55.157
- MAYBE WE MADE A MISTAKE.

18:03.832 --> 18:04.917
- HERE, LITTLE BROTHER.

18:05.000 --> 18:06.919
I CALL THIS
"THE TITO'S ISLAND

18:07.002 --> 18:08.879
CUP OF HAPPINESS
PICK-ME-UPPER."

18:12.966 --> 18:14.468
- [sighs]

18:14.551 --> 18:15.928
I JUST FEEL LIKE
EVERYONE DESERTED ME.

18:16.011 --> 18:19.473
- THEY DIDN'T
DESERT YOU, OTTO.

18:19.556 --> 18:22.017
- THEY KICKED ME OFF
THE TEAM FOR A BIG GAME,

18:22.100 --> 18:23.644
THEN LIED TO ME ABOUT IT.

18:23.727 --> 18:26.563
- THAT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE
THE LITTLE BROTHERS TO ME.

18:26.647 --> 18:27.856
EVER THINK YOUR BROKEN LEG
COULD BE THE REASON?

18:27.940 --> 18:29.817
- DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT THE REASON IS.

18:29.900 --> 18:32.528
MY OWN FRIENDS TURNED
ON ME.

18:32.611 --> 18:34.321
- HMM.

18:34.404 --> 18:36.907
THIS REMINDS ME
OF A SURF CONTEST I WAS IN ONCE,

18:36.990 --> 18:39.993
AND I RODE THIS MOST
INCREDIBLE WAVE,

18:40.077 --> 18:42.830
NAILED ALL MY MOVES,
GOT A PERFECT SCORE,

18:42.913 --> 18:44.414
AND WON FIRST PRIZE,

18:44.498 --> 18:47.125
AN ALL-EXPENSE-PAID
TWO-WEEK TRIP TO HAWAII.

18:50.879 --> 18:52.965
- AND?

18:53.048 --> 18:54.591
- AND THAT'S IT.

18:54.675 --> 18:56.552
I HAD A GREAT TIME.

18:56.635 --> 18:57.553
- WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO

18:57.636 --> 18:59.263
WITH YOUR FRIENDS
LETTING YOU DOWN?

18:59.346 --> 19:00.889
- NOTHING, REALLY.

19:00.973 --> 19:03.809
THEY SURE WERE
GOOD TIMES, THOUGH.

19:03.892 --> 19:05.227
- DAD!

19:05.310 --> 19:06.520
- LET ME TRY.

19:06.603 --> 19:08.355
OTTO, THE ANCIENT HAWAIIANS
HAD A SAYING.

19:08.438 --> 19:13.235
"THE BIRD THAT FLIES ALONE
IS THE GOOSE THAT GETS COOKED."

19:13.318 --> 19:15.279
- DOES THAT MEAN
THEY'RE ALL TURKEYS?

19:15.362 --> 19:18.198
- IT MEANS THAT FRIENDSHIPS
ARE MORE IMPORTANT

19:18.282 --> 19:19.992
THAN FOOLISH PRIDE.

19:20.075 --> 19:21.159
- YEAH.

19:21.243 --> 19:23.328
THEY SHOULD HEAR THAT.

19:23.412 --> 19:24.329
THANKS, DAD.

19:24.413 --> 19:27.165
THANKS, TITO.

19:27.249 --> 19:29.293
[players cheering]

19:35.924 --> 19:37.926
- WHOA,
CLOSE GAME.

19:38.010 --> 19:39.678
OH, YEAH!

19:44.641 --> 19:45.559
- YES!

19:45.642 --> 19:48.937
YEAH!

19:49.021 --> 19:51.607
[crowd cheering]

19:51.690 --> 19:55.110
- YEAH, WHOO!

19:55.193 --> 19:59.197
- LARS?

19:59.281 --> 20:00.616
I'M CALLING A TIMEOUT.

20:00.699 --> 20:03.201
[whistle blows]

20:03.285 --> 20:04.202
- OTTO?

20:04.286 --> 20:05.704
- DUDE?

20:05.787 --> 20:08.123
- WHAT'S WITH LARS?

20:08.206 --> 20:12.836
YOU REPLACED ME
WITH THAT GIANT MONKEY?

20:12.920 --> 20:15.797
- THERE ARE NO
GIANT MONKEYS.

20:15.881 --> 20:17.591
- BUT LARS?

20:17.674 --> 20:21.720
- BELIEVE ME,
IT WASN'T MY IDEA.

20:21.803 --> 20:22.804
- YOU GOT TO LET ME PLAY.

20:22.888 --> 20:25.307
I'M BETTER THAN THAT DORK.

20:25.390 --> 20:27.517
- WHAT DID YOU CALL ME?

20:27.601 --> 20:30.145
- WHY DO YOU WANT TO PLAY
WITH THESE KIDDIES ANYHOW?

20:30.228 --> 20:34.983
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
TOO COOL FOR US.

20:35.067 --> 20:36.026
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

20:36.109 --> 20:37.319
I'M OUT OF HERE.

20:37.402 --> 20:39.571
{\an8}LATER MUCH!

20:42.282 --> 20:44.451
- OTTO, YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

20:44.534 --> 20:45.994
LARS, COME BACK.

20:46.078 --> 20:47.663
- YES, I CAN.

20:47.746 --> 20:49.331
- BUT YOU DON'T HAVE BLADES.

20:49.414 --> 20:50.999
- I DON'T CARE.

20:51.083 --> 20:52.668
- AND YOUR LEG'S BROKEN.

20:52.751 --> 20:53.669
- DON'T WORRY.

20:53.752 --> 20:54.795
I GOT ANOTHER ONE.

21:00.759 --> 21:03.178
GAME ON.

21:03.595 --> 21:07.391
[all grunting]

21:20.946 --> 21:21.947
- [growls]

21:26.451 --> 21:28.203
UGH!

21:28.286 --> 21:31.999
- WHOA!

21:32.082 --> 21:34.793
- OWW!

21:40.048 --> 21:42.718
WHOA,

21:42.801 --> 21:43.885
WHAT HAPPENED?

21:43.969 --> 21:45.345
- OH, YOU'RE OKAY.

21:45.429 --> 21:49.141
- YES, MY HARDHEADED BROTHER
IS ALL RIGHT.

21:49.224 --> 21:50.892
- THAT MUST HAVE HURT.

21:50.976 --> 21:54.646
- YOU GOT TO BE TOUGH TO
BE A GOALIE, I ALWAYS SAY.

21:54.730 --> 21:55.897
- THE GAME.

21:55.981 --> 21:56.732
WHAT HAPPENED?

21:56.815 --> 22:00.152
- POSTPONED ON ACCOUNT
OF STUPIDITY.

22:00.235 --> 22:01.028
- BUT JUST FOR 24 HOURS.

22:01.111 --> 22:04.489
- I THOUGHT WE WERE
PLAYING TOMORROW.

22:04.573 --> 22:08.493
- COOL, THEN WE STILL
GOT A CHANCE.

22:08.577 --> 22:08.785
[all groan]

22:08.869 --> 22:10.579
- OTTO!

22:10.662 --> 22:12.414
- DAD, I DIDN'T
MEAN IT LIKE THAT.

22:12.497 --> 22:15.751
WHEN I SAID WE,
I MEANT YOU GUYS.

22:15.834 --> 22:17.210
all: WHEW.

22:17.294 --> 22:19.671
- I MEAN, I ONLY HAVE
TO GET HIT WITH THE PUCK ONCE

22:19.755 --> 22:20.881
BEFORE I GET THE POINT.

22:20.964 --> 22:22.090
- WHAT DID YOU GET THE SECOND
AND THIRD TIME?

22:22.174 --> 22:26.094
- AND YOU ALMOST
RE-BROKE YOUR LEG.

22:26.178 --> 22:27.262
- YEAH, THAT TOO.

22:27.346 --> 22:29.723
- STILL, YOU'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING.

22:29.806 --> 22:32.392
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

22:32.476 --> 22:34.352
- I'LL BE ROOTING
FOR YOU GUYS,

22:34.436 --> 22:35.604
EVEN THAT GIANT MONKEY.

22:35.687 --> 22:37.689
- GIANT MONKEYS!

22:37.773 --> 22:40.984
[screaming]

22:46.740 --> 22:48.658
PHEW.

22:53.121 --> 22:54.831
[screaming]

22:57.876 --> 23:00.837
[upbeat surf rock]

23:00.921 --> 23:09.012
{\an8}♪ ♪
